        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 1:57PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 155 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm with very
heavy rainfall over Forest City. This storm was nearly stationary.

Locations to be impacted include...
Forest City.

Very heavy rainfall rates up to 3 inches per hour will be possible
in these areas.
</description>
        <instruction>Very heavy rainfall may flood areas with poor drainage, such as
ditches and underpasses. Avoid these areas and do not cross flooded
roads. Water levels of small streams may also rise rapidly. Seek
higher ground if threatened by flood waters.</instruction>
